Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @ciabatta{1}.

Drain the @mozzarella{1%ball} and squeeze out as much liquid as you can. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}, then tear into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%grams} and onion. Fry until the mince has browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir in half the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%grams}, @Worcester sauce{15%grams}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water for the sauce{100%ml} (see pantry for both amounts) into the beef. Bring up to a boil, then lower to a simmer. Cook, until thickened slightly, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the gnocchi.

When boiling, add the @gnocchi{300%grams} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until the gnocchi rise to the surface of the water, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Lay your ciabatta halves onto a #baking tray{}, cut-side up.

Spread over the remaining @garlic clove{1}(chopped) and drizzle over the @pesto{32%grams}.

Once your sauce has thickened, stir through the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams} and gnocchi.

Transfer to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}. Top with the mozzarella. Pop alongside the ciabatta on the baking tray to catch the drips.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden and crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Share your ultimate Bolognese gnocchi bake between your serving plates. Add a handful of @wild rocket{20%grams} on the top.

Serve with your pesto garlic bread alongside. Enjoy!